# Tailscale auth key for the .sbx/tailscale kit.
#
# Copy to `.sbx/tailscale.env` (gitignored) and drop in a key, OR export TS_AUTHKEY
# in your environment before `sbx run`. The kit's startup reads env first, then this
# file. Never commit a real key — this repo is public.
#
# Create the key in the Tailscale admin console (Settings > Keys). For disposable
# sandboxes, use an auth key that is:
#   - Ephemeral        (node auto-removed when it goes offline — no stale devices)
#   - Reusable         (one key serves many sandbox launches)
#   - Pre-approved     (skip manual device approval if your tailnet requires it)
#   - Tagged           (e.g. tag:cofoundry — scope what the node can do via ACLs;
#                       see docs/setup.md for the tailnet ACL cofoundry uses)

TS_AUTHKEY=tskey-auth-xxxxxxxxxxxx-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
